    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect generator matrix selection due to const-correctness issue\n\n### Summary\nThe `choose_generator_matrix()` function was returning `short *` but internally casting away const qualifiers from the source arrays. This could lead to undefined behavior when the returned pointer was used.\n\nIn some edge cases with specific BG/Zc combinations, this caused incorrect shift values to be used during LDPC encoding, resulting in corrupted codewords that failed CRC checks.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure NR UE with BG=2 and Zc=64\n2. Transmit data with block length requiring lifting size 64\n3. Observe CRC failures on received data due to incorrect encoding\n4. Debug trace shows wrong shift values being applied in parity computation\n\nThe root cause was the explicit casts discarding const that could potentially corrupt memory access patterns.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_encoder/ldpc_generate_coefficient.c`: Updated function signature to return `const short *` and removed unsafe casts\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_encoder/ldpc_generate_coefficient.c`: Updated local variable types to maintain const-correctness\n\n"
}